This changes are for Ubuntu 18.04 LTS

# INITIAL ESSENTIALS
1. Update via Software Updater (make sure to stay in LTS).
2. Move user files to /home/<user>/ if needed.
3. Enable additional repository in "Software & Update"
4. Update Nvidia Graphics:
	```sudo ubuntu-drivers autoinstall```
4. Replace Nautilus with Nemo:
    ```
    sudo apt install nemo
    xdg-mime default nemo.desktop inode/directory application/x-gnome-saved-search    
    ```
5. Install the following:
	* build-essential
	* gnome-tweak-tool
	* communitheme
	* anaconda
	* vscode
	* ubuntu-restricted-extras
	* flatpak
	* gnome-software-plugin-flatpak

# GUI
* VSCode
* Meteo
* Calculator (Snap -> Deb)

# APT
* samba
* imagemagick
* sqlite3
* flatpak
* gnome-software-plugin-flatpak
* synaptic
* build-essentials
* cmake
* vim
* vim-gnome
* nvim
* openssh-server
* putty-tools
* zsh
	`chsh -s (which zsh); logout`
* powerline-fonts
* gnome-shell-extensions 
* chrome-gnome-shell
* dos2unix
* tree
* ffmpeg
* ubuntu-restricted-extras
* rename
* p7zip-full
* Windscribe
* qBittorrent
* xrdp 
* nvidia-xxx (need ppa)

# PIP (only those that have CLI)
* Pipenv

# NVM
* NodeJS & NPM (`nvm install node`)

# NPM
* pure-prompt

# Settings
* Application launcher animation (`gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.interface enable-animations false`)

* Change shell to zsh (`chsh -s zsh`)

# Fonts
* Menlo for Powerline (`/usr/local/share/fonts`)

# Others
* Anaconda
    * `conda config --set changeps1 False`
* oh-my-zsh
* zsh-nvm
* zsh-autosuggestions
* zsh-syntax-highlighting
* rc.local (`sudo systemctl enable rc-local`)
* CUDA 10
	[](https://www.linuxbabe.com/linux-server/how-to-enable-etcrc-local-with-systemd)
